LESIONS
Strengths
• Causal - brain area necessary
• Dramatic deficits: Phineas Gage, Tan, H.M., 
prosopagnosia
• Counterintuitive deficits: Blindsight, Category-Specific 
Deficits
• Dissociations
declarative memory (knowing that) & hippocampus 
procedural memory (knowing how) & basal ganglia

LESIONS
Limitations

• damage extensive, hard to localize, not 
systematic
• individual variability:
- case v.s. groups studies
• nearby systems likely to get injured together
• degeneration, recovery, compensation
• may offer limited views of normal brain 
functions

