RECORDING
EEG/ERP – Strengths & Limitations

Strengths
- great temporal resolution (10ms)
- extremely non-invasive
- relatively inexpensive

Limitations
- poor spatial resolution
- records large population of neurons
- “where is (are) the signal generators?”
- many trials needed for averaging

RECORDING
MEG - Principles
- Magnetoencephalography 

- active neurons produce 
small magnetic fields

- uses Superconducting 
Quantum Interference 
Devices (SQUIDs) to 
detect magnetic changes

- signals are 100 million 
time smaller than the 
earth's magnetic field

