RECORDING
MEG – Strength & Limitations

Strengths
- great temporal resolution (10ms, exactly like 
ERP)
- non-invasive
Limitations
- okay spatial resolution (better than ERP b/c  
magnetic signal does not get distorted going 
through skull/scalp, unlike electrical signal)
- many trials needed for averaging
- can only measure neurons parallel to the skull
- expensive ( > $1 million)

